Course Level Learning Analytics

Canvas Dashboard

Instructors at Harvard have access to advanced course level analytics based on student behavior in Canvas. Using a custom data pipeline built by VPAL-Research and HUIT, we surface a range of student and class level data. This includes video watching patterns (using data from LTI plugin providers) and analytics based on participation in discussion forums. Dashboards can be provisioned at scale and all protected behind Harvard Key in order to ensure that only instructors have access to identifiable student data.
